Most of the seminars are dedicated to academic discussions about the subjects of the thesis and also providing tips about academic writing skill and requirements.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Main objective of the master seminar is to direct students to a semiotic analysis of a problem (it can be a theoretical or practical object) and to test his/ her skills and abilities to discuss the matter. During the master seminar various skills of academic writing are taught. One of the aims of the master seminar is to provide a possibility for the students to assess each others subjects and the development of the thesis and also practice self-assessment.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course students will: 1)	be able to present ideas and discuss them in academic environment; 2)	manage to show creativeness in applying the semiotic methodology; 3)	choose a certain area of interest and delimit it for the thesis project; 4)	demonstrate the skills to use the academic literature for independent analysis; 5)	develop skills of oral presentation; 6)	understand the usefulness of peer assessment and self assessment.
